arcpbf 0.0.0.9000
  • Reference

    Extract body from response

    resp_body_pbf.Rd

    Responses of type application/x-protobuf are automatically processed using process_pbf() with optional post-processing applied.

    resp_body_pbf(resp, post_process = TRUE, use_sf = TRUE)

    Arguments

    resp

    A response object.

    post_process

    default TRUE. Apply post_process_pbf() to the pbf body.

    use_sf

    default TRUE. Whether or not to return an sf object.

    Details

    This function assumes the body is an Esri FeatureCollection protobuf. It does not support Knowledge Graph protobufs.

    See also

    Other httr2: multi_resp_process()

    Examples

    
if (rlang::is_installed("httr2")) {
  url <- "https://services.arcgis.com/P3ePLMYs2RVChkJx/arcgis/rest/services/ACS_Population_by_Race_and_Hispanic_Origin_Boundaries/FeatureServer/2/query?where=1=1&outFields=objectid&resultRecordCount=10&f=pbf&token="

  req <- httr2::request(url)
  resp <- httr2::req_perform(req)
  resp_body_pbf(resp)
}
